Without A Song ~ The Gaylords  (1955)  Mercury # MG 25198
(* The name "Gaylord" is a very old French surname. Ronald Fredianelli,  one of vocal groups founders, adopted the surname, becoming Ronnie Gaylord. He used it as his stage name for many years. The group was named after the French surname, although all the group members were themselves, of Italian lineage.)